duck: The Terminal, a 2004 film by Steven Spielberg, in which a man is trapped in an airport terminal
Terminal velocity in physics, the speed of an object when the restraining force exerted by a fluid (such as air) is equal to other forces (such as gravity) (see also Terminal velocity)
terminal definition: of or relating to an end, extremity, boundary, or terminus.
Terminal illness, a progressive disease that is expected to cause death
